 <text>
  <front>
   <head>SONG XXIII. Obedience to Parents.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">LET Children that would fear the LORD</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Hear what their Teachers say;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With Rev'rence meet their Parents Word,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And with Delight obey.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Have you not heard what dreadful Plagues</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Are threaten'd by the LORD,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To him that breaks his Father's Law,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Or mocks his Mother's Word?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">What heavy Guilt upon him lies!</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">How cursed is his Name!</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The Ravens shall pick out his Eyes,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And Eagles eat the same.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But those who worship GOD and give</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Their Parents Honour due,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Here on this Earth they long shall live,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And live hereafter too.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
